Message text: G/L Account <account> ist not defined in Chart of Account Chart of Account
Resolution: Account determination for tax Account keys should be configured usind dummy GL account DUMMYACDT, which is defined in A segment only.

Message text: Value <Cost Element  > of type <Cost Element > ID (ERP) in field <Cost Element> could not be mapped
Resolution: Check and complete MDG Mapping for Cost elements (Key Mapping).

Message text: Value <VendorNr > of type <Cost Center> ID (ERP) in field < Vendor> could not be mapped
Resolution: Check and complete MDG Mapping for Cost Centers (Key Mapping).

Message text: Inbound mapping failed for MWSKZ, value X, list ID MWSKZ/TAXUS, agency QS1CLNT100
Resolution:
Check and complete MDG mapping for Tax Codes (Value Mapping).
OR
Maintain the respective tax code mapping under both Tax Procedures

Message text: Value <CoCd> of type Company Code in field 'Tax company code' could not be mapped; see error xx
Resolution: Check and complete MDG Mapping for Company Codes (Key Mapping). Prerequisite: Company Code should be created in the central system with minimal configuration (T001 record is enough).

Message text: Account <account number> does not exist in company code <company code>
Resolution: Maintain the GL Account, in alignment with Chart of Account Team.

Message text: Vendor <vendor number> has no bank details with indicator <bank ID>
Resolution: Clear Bank Details indicator BSEG-BVTYP in mapping ("Mapping Action" = Clear)

Message text: Referenced invoice not yet posted (CC <company code>),<FY>, <Document Number>, Item xxx.
Resolution: Wait for next initial load run as it will likely get posted as soon as referenced document is successfully posted.

Message text: Referenced document not yet posted (Comp.Code xxxx, F.Year xxxx,<Document Number>)
Resolution: Wait for next initial load run as it will likely get posted as soon as referenced document is successfully posted.

Message text: Enter rate <currency 1> / <currency 2> rate type M for <date> in the system settings
Resolution: Exchange Rate configuration is imported from the Source system via ALE.

Message text: Company code <company code> is not set up for the payment transaction
Resolution: Make sure all the Payment attributes are cleared ("Mapping Action" = Clear)

Message text: House bank <bank id> is not defined in the paying company code <company code>
Resolution: Make sure that BSEG-HBKID, BSEG-HKTID are cleared ("Mapping Action" = Clear)

Message text: Bank <bank number> does not exist
Resolution: Make sure Bank information (BSEC-BANKN, BANKL, BANKS, IBAN) is cleared in CPD vendor/customer position.

Message text: Account <account number> requires an assignment to a CO object
Resolution: Correct GL Account Master record in target system accordingly.

Message text: Account  <account number> in company code <company code> is not a reconciliation account
Resolution:
Need to check below 2 scenario
1) Depending on the results of the analysis, correct the attribute "Reconciliation Account for" in all Company Codes (= for Chart of Account globally) or in particular ones (as exceptions)
2) GL mapping needs to check & maintained correctly

Message text: Payment block <payment block indicator> is not defined
Resolution: Define Payment Block in OB27

Message text: Error in account determination: table T030R key Chart of Account ESA
Resolution: (OB40) Automatic Account Determination for Transaction key (ESA). Also make sure that the Transaction Key is available in Tax Code Calculation Scheme.

Message text: Reconciliation account <account number> or short key <short key> is not permitted
Resolution:
GL Account Mapping (Key Mapping) as well as Special GL Indicator mapping (value mapping) and Special GL configuration in CFIN System should be consistent.
In case of Special GL posting: make sure that the GL account supplied matches with the one the system determines from the Special GL configuration.
In case of posting with Alternative Reconciliation Account (BSEG-XHKOM="X"), register the alternative account against customer's/vendor's "main" recons. account in the AP/AR configuration SPRO => Financial Accounting (New) => Accounts Receivable and Accounts Payable => Business Transactions => Postings with Alternative Reconciliation Account => Define Alternative Reconciliation Accounts

Message text: No code list configured for Type DTEL, GDT WT_WITHCD, List-ID    FE and Bus. Sys. XXXX
Resolution: Check and complete MDG mapping for Withholding Tax Codes (Value Mapping).

Message text: MDG mapping for CUSTOMER_ID Identifier 700016 is not unique
Resolution: Check and correct MDG Mapping for Customer (Key Mapping).

Message text: Posting keys for account determination for transaction YYY do not exist
Resolution: Posting keys maintained for all relevant keys related to concerned company codes

Message text: Payment term XXXX not defined
Resolution: Missing payment terms defined

Resolution: Maintain condition records in transaction FV 11
